This is an article about film censorship in the United Kingdom.

List of banned films
Main|List of banned films in the United Kingdom

Specific cases
*In Autumn 1972, Lord Longford and Raymond Blackburn decided to pursue a matter of pornography classification for the film Language of Love<ref name="Leigh">Rayment-hc|k|2|date=March 2012</ref> into the Court of Appeal of Lord Denning, MR, and lost the writ of mandamus against the Police Commissioner, who had refused to intrude upon the BBFC remit.<ref name=hs>cite news|title=Raymond Blackburn|url=http://www.heraldscotland.com/sport/spl/aberdeen/raymond-blackburn-1.814584|accessdate=1 September 2012|newspaper=The Herald|date=5 November 1991</ref><ref>[http://www.lawjournal.mcgill.ca/userfiles/other/8090603-burns.pdf (1975) 21 McGill L.J. 269: "Private Prosecutions in Canada: The Law and a Proposal for Change" (Burns)]</ref><ref>Reported as [1973] 1 Q.B. 241 (C.A.)</ref>
*In 1999, British television network ITV (TV network)|ITV broadcast a censored version of the British war film ''The Dam Busters (film)|The Dam Busters'' (1955), with all instances of the name of a dog called "Nigger (dog)|Nigger" removed. ITV blamed regional broadcaster London Weekend Television, which in turn alleged that a junior staff member had been responsible for the unauthorised cuts. When ITV again showed a censored version in June 2001, it was criticised by ''Index on Censorship'' as "unnecessary and ridiculous" and because the edits introduced continuity errors. The code word "nigger" transmitted in Morse Code upon the successful completion of the central mission was not censored.
*The 2004 film ''Black Friday (2004 film)|Black Friday'' was released in the United Kingdom with 17 seconds of the cockfighting scenes deleted. Laws in the UK do not allow any film footage of actual Cruelty to animals#Film making|animal cruelty that has been deliberately orchestrated by film-makers within the UK.<ref name= imdbaltversions>[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0400234/alternateversions Alternate versions for ''Black Friday''] from IMDb</ref>

